<h1>Honey Soy Thighs</h1>

<div class="time">Estimated Time to Completion: 25–30 minutes</div>

<h2>Equipment</h2>
<ul>
<li>Stovetop</li>
<li>Large skillet or pan</li>
<li>Mixing bowl</li>
<li>Tongs or spatula</li>
</ul>

<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>1.5–2 lbs boneless chicken thighs</li>
<li>¼ cup soy sauce</li>
<li>2 tbsp honey</li>
<li>1 tbsp brown sugar (optional but helps glaze)</li>
<li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
<li>1 tsp ginger (optional)</li>
<li>1 tbsp water</li>
<li>1 tbsp olive oil</li>
</ul>

<h2>How To</h2>
<ol>
<li>Prepare sauce: In a bowl mix soy sauce, honey, brown sugar, garlic, ginger, and water.</li>
<li>Heat pan: Add olive oil to a skillet over medium heat.</li>
<li>Cook chicken: Place chicken thighs in the pan and cook 5–6 minutes per side until browned.</li>
<li>Add sauce: Pour honey soy sauce into the pan with the chicken.</li>
<li>Simmer: Let the sauce cook 5–10 minutes until it thickens and coats the chicken.</li>
<li>Finish: Spoon the glaze over the chicken while it reduces.</li>
<li>Serve hot.</li>
</ol>

